"Customer Information" shall mean any data or information which relates to an individual or any other person (including but not limited to the Bank staff and customers) or which is held by or is under the control of any member of the Bank. Customer Information shall further include any of the following information when collected or accessed (whether given by a Bank staff/ customer/ the Bank/ any person authorised by a Bank customer, obtained by the Merchant from any third party or system generated/ accessed/ collected or otherwise or whether accessed by the Merchant or on its behalf during provision of any Services to the Bank pursuant to this Agreement) in the process of or pursuant to provision of any Services provided by the Merchant, disclosed/shared by or on behalf of the Bank to the Merchant and the Merchant shall as the receiving party therefor be obligated to observe all the obligations under the confidentiality related provisions under this Agreement and be liable thereunder:
Personal information; and/or
Sensitive personal data or information.
‘Personal information’ shall mean any information, which either directly or indirectly, in combination with other information available or likely to be available with a body corporate or received from any third-party provider and is capable of identifying such person including but not limited to his/her name, age, gender, address, email address, telephone/ mobile number etc. 
‘Sensitive personal data or information” shall mean such personal information which consists of information relating to:
Password;
Contacts;
Data scraped/ collated/ gathered from other third party websites visited;
Financial information or account related information including but not limited bank account details or credit card or debit card or other payment instrument details;
Educational qualifications; 
Work Credentials; 
Employment details;
Income details;
Records and history; 
Biometric information;
Physical, physiological and mental health condition;
Sexual orientation;
Medical records and history; 
Any other type of information as may be specified by the Bank from time to time;
Any other information/ type of information which would be covered under the “sensitive personal data or information” under Applicable Law from time to time.

The Merchant shall (and shall ensure that its employees, agents and subcontractors shall) be required to maintain such administrative, technical and physical safeguards, and such processes, procedures and checks, to secure the Customer Information, as may be required under Applicable Law and/or industry standards or regulations issued by any Governmental Authority, which safeguards must be at least equal to or better than (a) the safeguards it currently has in place to protect its own data; and (b) generally accepted security standards in the financial service industry.
The administrative, technical and physical safeguards, processes, procedures and checks as provided for in this Clause I (Data Security) will be designed to: 
protect the security and confidentiality of the Customer Information in the Merchant’s possession;
ensure against any anticipated threats or hazards to the security and confidentiality of the Customer Information; 
protect against unauthorised access to or use of the Customer Information or associated records which could result in substantial harm or inconvenience to the Bank; and 
ensure the proper and secure disposal of such data. 
Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Merchant shall initiate all measures which a prudent organisation, in a similar situation, would take to secure and defend its systems that contain the Customer Information and/or which are utilised for the provision of the Services against “hackers” and others who may seek, without authorisation, to modify or access the Customer Information. The Merchant will periodically test its internal and external systems for potential areas where security could be breached.
The Merchant covenants that it shall take appropriate technical and organisational measures against (i) any unauthorised or unlawful processing or alteration of the Customer Information, at any point in time where the Customer Information is being received, processed, reviewed, stored or transferred by the Merchant, (ii) any resultant loss or destruction of, or damage to, the Customer Information due to unauthorised processing or alterations, and (iii) unauthorised or accidental access, processing, erasure, transfer, use, modification, disclosure, or other misuse of the Customer Information and shall ensure that only authorised personnel bound by adequate confidentiality obligations shall have access to the Customer Information and strictly on a ‘need to know’ basis strictly limited to the extent required to perform the Merchant’s obligations hereunder.
The Merchant shall (including its employees, agents and subcontractors) in respect of the Customer Information:
comply with any reasonable and commercially viable request made or direction given by any personnel of the Bank in connection with the requirements of any data protection laws; 
not do or permit anything to be done which might jeopardise or contravene the terms of any registration, notification or authorisation under any data protection laws; 
not to process any data (including personal or private information of personnel, clients or customers of the Bank), as part of maintenance unless it is acting on the express instructions of the Bank, and such data shall be treated as Confidential Information, for the purpose of this Agreement; 
use the Customer Information only for the purposes of fulfilling its obligations under this Agreement and to comply with instructions given by the Bank from time to time in connection with use of such data and records, and not retain the data and records for any longer than is necessary for these purposes;
not transfer Customer Information which is in the possession of the Merchant, outside India, or allow persons outside India to have access to it, without the prior written approval of the Bank; 
take all reasonable steps to ensure the reliability of the personnel which will have access to the Customer Information and ensure that the personnel of the Merchant, who access the Customer Information give a written undertaking not to access, use, disclose or retain the Customer Information except in performing its duties of employment and is informed that failure to comply with this undertaking may be a criminal offence and may also lead the Bank, the Merchant to take disciplinary action against the employee; 
observe the provisions of, and comply with any request made or direction given by the Bank in connection with any data protection laws; and
consider all suggestions by the Bank to ensure that the level of protection provided for the Customer Information is in accordance with this Agreement including making such changes as may be suggested by the Bank, if any at its own cost.
The Merchant must ensure that the Customer Information in the possession of the Merchant is not comingled with any other data including any data of its other customers or clients.
The Merchant acknowledges that any unauthorized access, destruction, alteration, addition or impediment to access or use of the data when stored in any computer, or the publication or communication or any document or any part thereof, by any person to whose knowledge or into whose possession or custody such data has come into (other than such persons to whom the Merchant is authorized to publish or disclose the document or any part thereof), may be a criminal offence; 
The Merchant shall indemnify the Bank and keep the Bank fully and effectively indemnified on demand, in respect of any type of liability, loss, damage, claim, demand, action, charge, cost (including legal/attorney fees), expenses and Taxes from time to time incurred by the Bank arising out of or in connection with any wrongful disclosure or misuse of data as a result of breach of this Clause I (Data Security).
Where the introduction, imposition or variation of any law, order or regulation or official directive or any change in the interpretation or application thereof by any competent authority makes it apparent that it is unlawful or impractical without breaching such law, order or regulation or official directive for the Merchant to give effect to its obligations under this Agreement, then notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, the Merchant shall immediately consult the Bank to agree on any revision of the terms and conditions of this Agreement reasonably required in view of such circumstances.  
The Merchant agrees that it will not disclose, use, lecture upon or publish any of the Bank’s Confidential Information, except as such disclosure, use or publication may be required in connection with its work on a "need-to know" basis or unless the Bank expressly authorizes such disclosure in writing. The Merchant recognizes that all information created / accessed / processed by it, shall remain the sole property of the Bank and shall be returned to the Bank upon termination of this Agreement. 
The Merchant agrees to be vigilant and to report any breach of this Clause I (Data Security), all violations of information security, any breaches in the security practices, control processes and checks of the Merchant and all suspected security events immediately to (a) the Bank’s Information Security Group at security.incident@hdfcbank.com and (b) the concerned representatives and employees of the Bank which interact with the Merchant on a regular basis in respect of the Services of such violation.
The Merchant further confirms and agrees that it shall at all times during the continuance of this Agreement:
comply with the provisions of the Information Technology Act, 2000 and the applicable rules thereunder including without limitation the Information Technology (Reasonable security practices and procedures and sensitive personal data or information) Rules, 2011;
comply with all notifications, guidelines, circulars, issued by the RBI, in relation to securing card transactions; and
monitor the security practices, control processes and checks in respect of any Customer Information and other Confidential Information received by the Merchant, on a regular basis.
The Merchant shall ensure complete security of all information in relation to the Services and shall be responsible therefor at all times when the people, processes, and decision making authority required to secure such information as well as the information itself are in its control and: 
the Customer Information is stored whether permanently or temporarily on the systems of the Merchant or any of its agents, sub-contractors or representatives;
